article.headline: SE Missouri 96, Murray St. 85
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Brandon Foust scored 23 points to lead Southeast Missouri to a 96-85 win over Murray State Monday night. Southeast Missouri (6-11, 4-4 Ohio Valley Conference) finished the first half with a 20-9 run for a 43-37 halftime lead and never trailed in the second half. Murray State (7-9, 5-3) cut the lead to six with 1:25 left to play but couldn't get any closer, as the Redhawks, coached by former Murray State coach Scott Edgar, held on for the win. The game was marred by four technical fouls and the ejection of Southeast Missouri's Michael Rembert in the second half. The game was spent largely at the free-throw line as Murray State committed 30 personal fouls while the Redhawks committed 29. The Racers jumped out to an early 13-7 lead behind seven points from Bruce Carter, who finished with 20. Southeast Missouri came back to tie the game at 13 before eventually taking a 22-20 lead as Johnny Hill came off the bench and hit two consecutive 3-pointers. Murray recovered the lead and stretched it to as much as five before the Redhawks' spurt began. David Johnson added 18 points for Southeast Missouri, Roderick Pearson had 17 and Hill 16. Tyler Hollway scored 24 points for Murray, and Ray George added 14.
